{
  "text": "Randomness recovery. We start with a definition of randomness recovery for public-key encryption. For any public-key encryption scheme PKE = (Kg, Enc, Dec) we specify an additional randomness recovery algorithm that takes a secret key sk and ciphertext c to return coins r; that is, we write PKE = (Kg, Enc, Dec, Rec). To our knowledge, this notion has been discussed informally in the literature (e.g. in [CITATION_1] ) but our formalization is novel. Suppose Enc draws its coins from Coins. We require that for all messages m \u2208 MsgSp(1 k )",
